to
the
language
of
another
mind.
Then,
too,
her
imagination
was
full
of
pictures
images
of
Moore,
scenes
where
he
and
she
had
been
together;
winter
fireside
sketches;
a
glowing
landscape
of
a
hot
summer
afternoon
passed
with
him
in
the
